  ${
    $d f k m x z F $.  $d f k m n z ph $.  $d f k m x z R $.  $d f k m x z X $.
    $d x y z A $.  $d k m n S $.
    supcvg.1 $e |- X e. _V $.
    supcvg.2 $e |- S = sup ( A , RR , < ) $.
    supcvg.3 $e |- R = ( n e. NN |-> ( S - ( 1 / n ) ) ) $.
    supcvg.4 $e |- ( ph -> X =/= (/) ) $.
    supcvg.5 $e |- ( ph -> F : X -onto-> A ) $.
    supcvg.6 $e |- ( ph -> A C_ RR ) $.
    supcvg.7 $e |- ( ph -> E. x e. RR A. y e. A y <_ x ) $.
    $( Extract a sequence ` f ` in ` X ` such that the image of the points in
       the bounded set ` A ` converges to the supremum ` S ` of the set.
       Similar to Equation 4 of [Kreyszig] p. 144.  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 15-Feb-2013.)  (The proof was shortened by Mario Carneiro,
       26-Apr-2014.) $)
    supcvg $p |- ( ph -> E. f ( f : NN --> X /\ ( F o. f ) ~~> S ) ) $=
      ( cn wcel cr vk vz vm cv wf cfv cle wbr wral wa wex ccom cli wrex clt wss
      wne w3a csup wceq wfo fof syl feq3 syl5ibcom f00 simprbi syl6 necon3d mpd
      c0 3jca adantr c1 cdiv cmin suprcl syl5eqel nnrecre resubcl fmptd ffvelrn
      co syl2an sylan oveq2 oveq2d ovex adantl crp nnrp rpreccl ltsubrp eqbrtrd
      fvmpt syl6breq suprlub syl12anc wi ssel2 ltle syl2anc reximdva wb rexeqdv
      crn forn wfn breq2 rexrn bitr3d mpbid ralrimiva nnenom fveq2 breq2d axcc4
      ffn cvv nnuz cz 1z a1i ad2antrr cc0 csn cmpt cc recnd eqimss2i climconst2
      cxp cuz nnex sylancl 0z mptex eqeltri eqeltrd ad3antrrr fvconst2g oveq12d
      ax-1cn divcnv eqid eqtr4d climsub subid1 breqtrd fex vex coexg fss fveq2d
      fco breq12d rcla4cva adantll wfun ffun simpllr simpr fvco3 syl3anc simplr
      breqtrrd syldan suprub syl6breqr climsqueeze ex imdistanda eximdv ) ARJGU
